Preheat your #oven to 200°C. Halve and deseed the @bell pepper{1}. Cut each half into 2 strips then put them skin side up on a separate #baking tray{} with a drizzle of @oil{} and season with @salt and @pepper. Roast on the middle shelf of the oven until soft and starting to char, ~{18-20%minutes}. 

Meanwhile, chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). Pop the chunks on a large, low sided, wide #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, then season with @salt and @pepper. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer. Once your oven is hot, roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Peel half of the @garlic cloves{2} and pop into #foil{} with a drizzle of oil and scrunch to enclose it. Roast on the same baking tray as the peppers until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @lemon{1}. Peel and grate the remaining garlic (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Trim the @green beans{150%g}. Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into small pieces.

Heat a large #frying pan{} over medium heat (no oil!). Once hot, add the @flaked almonds{25%g} and cook, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> Watch almonds like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Remove the almonds from the frying pan to a #bowl{} and return the pan to a medium high heat with a drizzle of @oil. When hot, add the @Serrano ham{2%slices} and cook until golden and crisp, ~{1-2%minutes} per side. Remove from the pan to a #plate{} and set aside.

Pop half of the almonds, the roasted peppers, roasted garlic, the remaining lemon juice, @olive oil{1} and half the @smoked paprika{1%tsp} in a #hand blender{} and blitz until you have a smooth sauce (if you do not have a hand blender you can finely chop the pepper and almond and combine with the rest of the ingredients in a bowl to make a salsa). Set aside.

Return the frying pan to a medium high heat with a splash of @oil (no need to wash). When hot, add the shallot and cook until soft, ~{3-4%minutes}. When the shallot has softened, add the green beans and a splash of @water to the pan, season with @salt and @pepper and cover the pan with a #lid{} or #tin foil{}. Cook until tender ~{4-6%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}. When cooked, squeeze in half the lemon juice and all the lemon zest and season to taste with @salt and @pepper. Remove from the heat and cover with a lid to keep warm.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of oil in another frying pan on a medium high heat. When hot, lay in the @monkfish medallions{200%g} and fry until golden brown and cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes} each side.

> The monkfish is cooked when opaque all the way through.

Sprinkle on the remaining smoked paprika and cook for a further ~{1%minute}. Remove the pan from the heat. Spoon the sauce on your plates (reheat first in a pan if you'd rather it was warm), top with the beans followed by the monkfish. Serve the potatoes along side. Top the fish with the Serrano ham and remaining almonds. Sprinkle over the parsley and Enjoy!